get-event-listener-list (self: class g2-event-listener-support) = (class item-list)
Return the current event listener list.

Remove-g2-event-listener (self: class g2-event-listener-support, listener : class g2-event-listener) = ()
Remove a G2-EVENT-LISTENER previously added using add-g2-event-Listener.

Add-g2-event-listener (self: class g2-event-listener-support, listener : class g2-event-listener) = ()
Add a G2-EVENT-LISTENER to internal listener list, duplicates are ignored.

g2:c.METHOD.g2:a.TEXT:
add-g2-event-listener(self: class g2-event-listener-support, listener : class g2-event-listener)
begin
insert listener at the end of the _event-listeners of self;
end

g2:c.BORDERLESS-FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT:
G2-EVENT-CREATE-EVENT (event-class: class class-definition, source : class item) = (class g2-event-object)
Always use this procedure to create instances of G2-EVENT-OBJECTs (or any subclasses), it ensures that the source of the event is set correctly.
G2-EVENT-OBJECT must be the superior of any event class that may be passed to a listener method defined in a G2-EVENT-LISTENER subclass.
This class is the superior of any G2 Event Listener classes.
